HEADWORD: Taranis
<hw>Tar"a*nis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>taranis</ets>, from the Celtic; cf. W. & Corn. <ets>taran</ets>
thunder.]</ety> <fld>(Myth.)</fld> <def>A Celtic divinity, regarded as
the evil principle, but confounded by the Romans with Jupiter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tarantass</ent>⟦br⟧
